Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Location Manager - Old Post Office Branch (Full-Time, Permanent) Cambridge , ON Description Posting #23-50x Location Manager Full-time, Permanent Old Post Office BranchIdea Exchange is a community hub comprised of the public libraries and art galleries for the City of Cambridge, a thriving city with a rich architectural heritage and the second largest community within the Waterloo Region. We are committed to supporting and inspiring our community in the exploration of reading, arts, innovation, and learning.Under the general direction of the Director, Public and Digital Services, the Location Manger is responsible for the daily operations of the location: for providing leadership and supervision to location staff, for ensuring community engagement and a vibrant response to community needs; and for the overall operating effectiveness of the location, in alignment with the organization’s strategic plan. They resolve member issues referred from front line staff and are responsible for the unique needs of the location including maintaining relationships with external partners and ensuring the successful delivery of library services.What You’ll DoAs Location Manager, you will:Manage the daily operations and activities of the location.Hire, train, supervise, and evaluate all public service employees and volunteers at the location in accordance with the Human Resources policies of the organization.Empower and support employees to deliver effective, high quality library service.Manage the location’s physical collections, including the maintenance, deselection and promotion of all materials. Responsible for addressing the conduct of members and visitors that violates Idea Exchange’s Code of Conduct.Oversee the emergency preparedness and Health and Safety requirements of the location. Communicates and promotes this to employees and members of the public.Facilitate or conduct adult programming and group tours at the location in coordination with the Outreach and Programming Team.Responsible for communicating facility needs or issues with internal support services.Act as a collaborative and active member of the leadership team. Recommends changes in service delivery and participate in the development of library policies and procedures.Provide a variety of professional librarian services to members, including advanced reference, advisory, and research services.Support the development, piloting and implementation of new programs and services to meet community needs.Develop children, youth and adult programs consistent with the organization’s programming goals and needs of the location.Build and develop relationships with the community to ensure library services are responsive to community needs and interests. Participate as required in meetings with outside agencies and institutional partners to promote Idea Exchange.Responsible for monitoring location specific budgets.Undertakes system wide projects and other duties as requested.What You’ll Need to SucceedTo be qualified for and successful in the role, you should have:Required - University Masters of Library and/or Information Science or related master’s degreeRequired – Prior related experience: 4 YearsRequired – Experience working in a library at a professional level – 4 YearsRequired – Experience working in a leadership capacity in a professional library setting – 2 yearsRequired - Demonstrated intermediate proficiency with task-specific software such as Microsoft Office Suite (Word, Excel, Outlook)Preferred – Experience working in a public libraryProven ability to confidently coach others to achieve service improvementAbility to serve members of the public, maintaining positivity and enthusiasm in a busy work environment with frequent interruptionsSkilled at making customer service a top priority while using good judgement and empathy when applying library policiesView the organization as a unified team and have experience resolving interpersonal conflictAre highly-organized, and able to carry out job functions with flexibility, creativity and initiativeStrong analytical skills and a keen attention to detailAbility to maintain confidentiality of sensitive informationExcellent multitasking skills and ability to complete responsibilities on timeExceptional verbal and written communication, critical thinking, and problem-solving skillsSuperior organization and time management skills to address competing prioritiesDemonstrated ability to collaborate professionally with internal and external partnersA passion for supporting the diverse interests and needs of the Cambridge communityWhat We OfferWorking at Idea Exchange offers you the opportunity to be part of an organization that is welcoming, collaborative, and passionate about the community.We provide fair market compensation, excellent health, dental and vision benefits, consistent and reliable work schedules, paid sick time and free parking. We also offer participation in the OMERS pension plan.Pay: Starting rate is $84,101 per year (level 12 in our salary grid - 2023 rate)Hours: 70 hours in a two-week period.Schedule: Days, weekends and evenings may be requiredNote: schedules are service-driven and as such are subject to change.How to ApplyTo be considered for the position, please apply by December 5, 2023Tell us why we should consider you for this position! Please provide both a cover letter and resume, combined as a single PDF document.Submit your application by email to recruitment@ideaexchange.orgIf applying by email, please quote “23-50x Location Manager” in your email subject line.The anticipated start date for this position is January 2024The position is open to internal and external candidates. We thank everyone for their interest, however only those candidates selected for an interview will be contacted.Additional InformationIdea Exchange aspires to employ a staff complement that fully represents the diversity of the community we serve. All qualified individuals who would contribute to the further diversification of our organization are encouraged to apply.Idea Exchange is an equal opportunity employer and is committed to accommodating individual needs in accordance with the Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act (AODA). If you require any accommodations at any point during the application and hiring process, please contact Human Resources at hr@ideaexchange.org.A Security Clearance Check with Vulnerable Sector Screening will be required. Compensation $84,101 per year Closes: 5 December, 2023 Idea Exchange Cambridge , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
