Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Librarian - Reference and Instruction Kelowna , BC Description OKANAGAN COLLEGEOkanagan College transforms lives and communities. We are one of Canada's leading colleges. We create outstanding educational experiences for our learners, both students and employees. We work and learn in a welcoming and caring culture. We are a catalyst for change through collaboration with our learners and partners. We serve, lead and anticipate the social, economic and environmental needs of communities.Position Title:Librarian - Reference and InstructionCompetition Number:C002623Division/Portfolio:Library ServicesDepartment/Program:LibraryCampus/Centre:KelownaYour Opportunity:Under the general direction of the Director of Library Services, is responsible for working with students and faculty in the provision of Library reference and instruction services, liaison to one or more instructional departments, preparation of guides and tutorials, and representing the Library at campus events. Other duties may include professional development and service.Education and Experience:Minimum qualification is a degree from an accredited Master’s program in Library and Information Studies.Experience in the provision of library reference and instruction services.Experience assisting library users with both print and electronic resources, including creating instructional materials in a variety of formats.Recent experience in an academic library is preferredFunctions and Duties:1. Provides reference services, in person, by email, and in a real-time virtual environment.2. Prepares and delivers in-class instruction to students, in conjunction with other librarians.3. Acts as liaison to one or more instructional departments to ensure that Library collections and services meet instructional and student needs.4. Prepares guides and tutorials about research and the use of Library collections and services, using a variety of media and formats.5. In collaboration with the Campus Librarian and other Library Services and OC employees, represents Library Services at OC and Library campus events and activities.6. Engages in professional development activity intended to promote subject area and technical competence in librarianship and information science.7. Engages in service activities that support the College and/or the profession and/or the community.8. Other related Librarian duties.Skills and Abilities:Familiar with, and supportive of, new and emerging technologies in library services; comfortable in a computerized environment.Strong oral and written communication skills.Ability to promote contact and communication among students and faculty.Ability to work independently, and as part of a team, to assist in the delivery of library services.Ability to work with people of diverse educational and socio-cultural backgrounds.Strong organizational skills in managing multiple activities and working under time constraints.Demonstrated ability to learn new skills.Demonstrated ability to teach in a variety of situations, across a diversity of subjects and program levels, and using a variety of methods, including active learning.Some evening and weekend work may be required.Appointment Type:Faculty - Full-time TermAppointment Start Date:01/02/2024Appointment End Date:05/31/2024Schedule:35 hours per week, Monday through FridaySome evenings and weekend work may be required from time to time.Annual Salary/Hourly Rate:Salary range $69,753 to $111,776 with normal starting salary between $76,574 and $83,395 annually*, dependent on relevant education and experience. *Note: Part-time Term and summer appointments subject to adjustment factors as per the collective agreementSpecial Instructions to Applicants:For more information about the position, including a full job description, please contact the Hiring Committee Chairperson, Roën Janyk, at rjanyk@okanagan.bc.ca, or Eva Gavaris, the Department Chair, at egavaris@okanagan.bc.ca.Posting Opening Date:11/24/2023Posting Closing Date:12/10/2023APPLICATIONS:To apply for this position, please go to our employment site: https://www.employmentopportunities.okanagan.bc.ca and complete an on-line application. All applications must be submitted through our employment site to be considered.Okanagan College is committed to increasing the equitable and inclusive participation of marginalized people in all aspects of college life. We welcome and encourage applications from Indigenous Peoples, Black People, members of racialized groups/visible minorities, people with disabilities and people with diverse gender identities or expressions. People with disabilities who anticipate needing accommodations for any part of the application process may contact, in confidence, AccessibilityHR@okanagan.bc.ca Compensation Salary range $69,753 to $111,776 with normal starting salary between $76,574 and $83,395 annually*, dependent on relevant education and experience. *Note: Part-time Term and summer appointments subject to adjustment factors as per the collective agreement Closes: 10 December, 2023 Okanagan College Kelowna , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
