on-making of the ministries’ staff and to support the delivery of health and child welfare services throughout the province. The position has significant latitude and considerable freedom to act in developing innovative approaches to accessing and disseminating information. This position is responsible for fostering strong cooperative relationships with branches in the ministries to coordinate efforts, reduce overlap and effectively use and develop resources. Qualifications for this role include: Master of Library Science degree, or equivalent, from an accredited university; Five years' experience in a management or supervisory level in a special library; and Five years' experience in budgeting and planning. For more information and to apply online by December 10, 2023, please go to: https://bcpublicservice.hua.hrsmart.com/hr/ats/Posting/view/107458 Compensation $88,152.35 - $100,665.30 annually Closes: 10 December, 2023 Ministry of Health Victoria , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
